NAME
	wiggle

SYNOPSYS
	wiggle [bottom]
	wiggle [bottom] <adverb>
	wiggle finger [at] <target>
	wiggle finger <adverb> [at] <target>

DESCRIPTION
	If you enter wiggle without arguments, or explicitly wiggle your
        bottom, you will wiggle just that. Alternatively, you can wiggle
	your finger at someone or something.

OPTIONS
        finger   - wiggle your finger at someone or something.
        [bottom] - wiggle your bottom, default if used without a target.
	<adverb> - any adverb from the available set or a period . to not
		   not use an adverb at all.
	<target> - the target or targets you want to perform the emotion
		   on. This may be a name or description of a living or
		   livings, ie. Mercade, the dwarf wizard and dwarves are
		   all valid targets.
                   This emote can also be performed on non-living items.

DEFAULT ADVERB
	without default adverb

SEE ALSO
	adverbs emotions
